\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-account-768x104-1-60x8.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-account-768x104-1-150x20.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 659px) 100vw, 659px\" \/><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the left menu Account area\u00a0click on &#8220;<strong>Settings<\/strong>&#8220;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"222\" height=\"226\" class=\" wp-image-845 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-account-settings-2.png\" alt=\"authorize.net perfex crm\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-account-settings-2.png 185w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-account-settings-2-60x60.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-account-settings-2-148x150.png 148w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 222px) 100vw, 222px\" \/><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on <strong>API credentials<\/strong> area located in the security settings<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"644\" height=\"189\" class=\" wp-image-846 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-api-credentials-768x224-3-300x88.png\" alt=\"authorize.net perfex crm\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-api-credentials-768x224-3-300x88.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-api-credentials-768x224-3.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-api-credentials-768x224-3-60x18.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-net-api-credentials-768x224-3-150x44.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 644px) 100vw, 644px\" \/><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You will need to get <strong>API Login ID &amp; \u00a0Transaction Key, <\/strong>your API Login ID will be displayed on the current page<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"668\" height=\"563\" class=\" wp-image-847 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-api-login-id-4-300x253.png\" alt=\"authorize.net perfex crm\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-api-login-id-4-300x253.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-api-login-id-4-60x51.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-api-login-id-4-150x127.png 150w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/authorize-api-login-id-4.png 749w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 668px) 100vw, 668px\" \/><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get\u00a0a new <strong>Transaction Key<\/strong>, you will need to answer the security question at the bottom of the page below the Create New Key(s) section, check the &#8220;Disable Old transaction Key(s)&#8221; checkbox and press Submit.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Copy your API Login ID, Transaction Key,  and <strong>Public Key<\/strong> then add them to the settings area for Payment gateways in Perfex CRM<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Notes<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Authorize.NET supports only <strong>1 currency per account<\/strong>, in the currency field add only 1 currency eq: USD or AUD, etc..<\/li><li>If you enabled <strong>test mode<\/strong>, read more <a href=\"https:\/\/developer.authorize.net\/hello_world\/testing_guide\/.html\">here<\/a>.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>To configure Authorize.net Accept.js payment gateway, you need to navigate to the payment gateways configuration page in Setup->Settings->Payment->Gateways and click on the Authorize.net Accept.js tab. Public Key Before using Accept.js, you must generate a Public Client Key. To generate the Public Key, log in to the Merchant Interface as a